You can’t do it on your own anymore”.</p></div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f549113e5\">Current statistics from the SSA estimate that the average wait time for a hearing is 602 days or 1.6 years. For people like John, receiving a denial because the application was not completed correctly might have added months onto the wait time for approval.</p></div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f549113e5\">Every month of waiting drains even more from his savings account. “My bills were piling up and I could not sleep at night, constantly worrying about not being able to provide for my family, I did not want to screw up on the appeals and have to wait longer” said John.</p></div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f549113e5\">He finally gave into the ads he was seeing online for the disability advocacy group, <strong><em>Disability Freedom</em></strong>. “The thoughts that ran through my mind were fears that using an attorney would cost too much and they would drain me even more, I just could not afford it.”</p></div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\" data-css=\"tve-u-15f549629d7\"><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f549113e5\">What many people are surprised to find out, is that disability attorneys and advocate groups, like the one John used, only get paid a small percentage of back disability payments only after you win your approval. You only pay if you win. The payment is <a href=\"http://usadisabilitylaw.com/social-security-disability-attorney-fees-what-does-it-cost/\">capped by law</a> to 25% up to $6,000.00.This is one of the major reasons why advocacy groups are <em>extremely selective</em> in the cases they take on.</p></div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f549113e5\">If a person never receives approval for disability benefits, they don’t have to pay a dime. “For me I didn’t mind paying someone after I won approval if it meant peace of mind.”, John said. “It was like I could finally sleep at night knowing that there was a group fighting for me, making sure everything was done correctly”.</p></div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f549113e5\">Although disability advocacy groups cannot guarantee a quicker approval, they can reduce the time lost having to refile due to technical errors, which as mentioned above, is one of the major reasons for first time denials. “I’m happy with how everything turned out” said John. “If I was going through this process again, I would get on the phone with an advocacy group right away to see if they could help, it would have saved me months of unnecessary anxiety”.</p></div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f549113e5\">To learn more about advocacy groups like the one mentioned in this article, <a href=\"https://www.disability-benefits-help.org/cpc/about-ssdi?utm_source=google&amp;utm_medium=cpc&amp;utm_term=disability%20benefits&amp;utm_content=225101598144&amp;utm_campaign=SSD+-+Phrase+Always&amp;__egma[MatchType]=p&amp;__egma[Network]=g&amp;__egma[Device]=c&amp;__egma[Creative]=225101598144&amp;__egma[Placement]=&amp;__egma[AdPosition]=1t1&amp;gclid=EAIaIQobChMI-_2d2KaM1wIVF7jACh0fsQS1EAAYASAAEgId3_D_BwE\"><u>click here</u></a></p></div>'),(840,76,'tve_revision_tve_has_wistia_popover','0'),(841,77,'thrive_post_fonts','[]'),(842,77,'tcb2_ready','1'),(843,77,'_edit_lock','1509549391:1'),(844,77,'_edit_last','1'),(847,78,'tve_revision_tve_landing_page',''),(848,78,'tve_revision_tve_content_before_more',''),(849,78,'tve_revision_tve_content_more_found',''),(850,78,'tve_revision_tve_save_post',''),(851,78,'tve_revision_tve_custom_css',''),(852,78,'tve_revision_tve_user_custom_css',''),(853,78,'tve_revision_tve_page_events',''),(854,78,'tve_revision_tve_globals',''),(8