p://ssclaimadvocates.com\" data-css=\"tve-u-15f82cc5c11\"></a></h1></div></div>\n</div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv-button\" data-css=\"tve-u-15f82cf36d6\">\n<a href=\"http://ssclaimadvocates.com/\" class=\"tcb-button-link\" onclick=\"ga(\'send\',\'event\',\'clicks\',\'SSClaim_Advocates_Button_Click\',\'SSDI_Leads\');return\" true;\"\"=\"\">\n<span class=\"tcb-button-texts\"><span class=\"tcb-button-text thrv-inline-text\"><u>Click To Qualify</u></span></span>\n</a>\n</div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><p><span data-css=\"tve-u-15f82c9ed24\" style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Or call them directly to have your questions answered even faster:</span>\n<a data-css=\"tve-u-15f82c9bfce\" href=\"tel:8554820729\">1-855-482-0729</a></p></div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv-page-section\">\n<div class=\"tve-page-section-out\" data-css=\"tve-u-15f73c2f915\"></div>\n<div class=\"tve-page-section-in tve_empty_dropzone\" data-css=\"tve-u-15f73c2a4e4\"><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\" data-css=\"tve-u-15f73c67d17\"><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f73c64b30\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><u>Advertiser Disclosure:&nbsp;&nbsp;</u>SSDInsider is a consumer information site that offers free articles and information relating to Social Security Disability. Many of the companies whose services we mention provide us compensation when someone who clicks from our site becomes their customer. This is how we make money to support our site. Compensation may impact which companies we write about and which articles those companies appear. We do not mention all companies that provide a given service All opinions expressed on this site are our own.</p></div></div>\n</div>'),(957,82,'tve_revision_tve_landing_page',''),(958,82,'tve_revision_tve_content_before_more','<div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f6e66d4d2\"><strong>Time Required:</strong> 2 Minutes<br><br>“You never think it will happen to you – and then it does.”John Sterling is recalling his reaction when he received the news that he would never return to work.</p><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f6e66d4d2\">&nbsp;But Sterling wasn’t laid off – he was one of 375,000 Americans every year who are retired by their doctors for disabilities. He, like many Americans, never planned for the abrupt brain aneurysm that would change his life.</p><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f6e66d4d2\">The government, however, does plan, and a tiny percentage of Sterling’s wages have been paid into the Disability Insurance Trust Fund since the program was begun in 1956. “I thought it would be easy to apply for disability benefits, because I’ve been contributing my whole life,” Sterling said, trying to hide a grimace.</p><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f6e66d4d2\">“Boy, was I wrong.”</p><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f6e66d4d2\">He said he struggled with the application, and after he submitted it and was awaiting good news, he received a letter of denial in the mail citing a lack of hard medical evidence in his case.</p><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f6e66d4d2\">“My doctor told me I was unable to go back to my job,” Sterling said. “He’s my doctor. What more medical evidence do they need?”</p><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f6e66d4d2\">Unfortunately, John Sterling’s situation is far from uncommon. Data collected from the Social Security Administration (SSA) shows that roughly 68 percent of first-time disability applicants are initially denied.</p><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f6e66d4d2\">While differing from case to case, the reasons for these denials commonly involve incorrect or incomplete applications with a lack of information. Given just 60 days to apply for an appeal, Sterling said he felt crushed and overwhelmed.</p></div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element\"><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f6e66d4d2\">&nbsp;“I’m a responsible citizen. I couldn’t understand why the government wasn’t willing to help me.” </p></div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\" data-css=\"tve-u-15f6e6b1606\"><h4 class=\"\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><strong>“I’m a responsible citizen. I couldn’t understand why the government wasn’t willing to help me.”</strong></em></h4></div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f6e66d4d2\">Current data from the SSA estimates wait times for appeal hearings to take over 600 days, or nearly 20 months.&nbsp;</p><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f6e66d4d2\">Every month of waiting was another month that Sterling was pulling from his life’s reserves to cover daily expenses, slowly draining his savings account. “I wasn’t sleeping, I was constantly worrying,” Sterling said.&nbsp;</p><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f6e66d4d2\">“I was the breadwinner, and I needed to be able to provide for my family. It killed me that I wasn’t able to do that.”In need of another option, Sterling turned online for legal advice. “A friend recommended I look for an advocacy group, but that sounded expensive. I already couldn’t afford my bills,” he said. “I certainly didn’t think I could afford help.”</p><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f6e66d4d2\">But online, he learned that disability attorneys and advocate groups such as Disability United are paid only a small percentage of back disability payments, and only after a client’s application is approved.</p><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f6e66d4d2\">These payments are capped at 25 percent and limited to $6,000 by law. For this reason, many advocacy groups are extremely selective about their clients, and they take cases that they expect to win. If their client is never approved for disability benefits, the client doesn’t pay a dime.</p><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f6e66d4d2\">And though disability advocacy does not guarantee a faster approval process, professional groups like these can vastly reduce the time lost due to technical errors and refiling—one of the top reasons for first-time denials—and greatly improve the chances of a favorable outcome.</p><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f6e66d4d2\">Sterling said he didn’t mind paying after the approval for the immense peace of mind he gained. “Knowing that I had a group of experts fighting for my case meant that I could finally sleep at night.</p><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f6e66d4d2\">I gave myself the best chance of a good outcome.”The best outcome was what Sterling, and the many other disability applicants every year who seek out help, received. Advocacy groups and disability attorneys build sophisticated cases for their clients to ensure that applications make it through all the hoops, and in today’s complex system, it truly takes an expert.</p><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f6e66d4d2\">“You can’t do it on your own these days,” Sterling said. “My advocacy group gave me so much help and reassurance. I could have saved myself months of unnecessary anxiety if I had just known that sooner.”</p><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f6e66d4d2\">If you want to learn more about advocacy groups like Disability United to see if they can help you or a loved one, click here.</p></div>'),(959,82,'tve_revision_tve_content_more_found',''),(960,82,'tve_revision_tve_save_post',''),(961,82,'tve_revision_tve_custom_css','@media (min-width: 300px){[data-css=\"tve-u-15f6e6b1606\"] { margin-top: 0px !important; padding-top: 0px !important; margin-bottom: 30px !important; }#tve_editor [data-css=\"tve-u-15f6e66d4d2\"] { font-size: 17px !important; }[data-css=\"tve-u-15f6e66d4d2\"] { line-height: 1.75em !important; }}'),(962,82,'tve_revision_tve_user_custom_css',''),(963,82,'tve_revision_tve_page_events','a:0:{}'),(964,82,'tve_revision_tve_globals',''),(965,82,'tve_revision_tve_global_scripts',''),(966,82,'tve_revision_thrive_icon_pack',''),(967,82,'tve_revision_thrive_tcb_post_fonts',''),(968,82,'tve_revision_tve_has_masonry',''),(969,82,'tve_revision_tve_has_typefocus',''),(970,82,'tve_revision_tve_updated_post','<div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f6e66d4d2\"><strong>Time Required:</strong> 2 Minutes<br><br>“You nev