ion_tve_global_scripts',''),(2952,191,'tve_revision_thrive_icon_pack','0'),(2953,191,'tve_revision_thrive_tcb_post_fonts','a:0:{}'),(2954,191,'tve_revision_tve_has_masonry','0'),(2955,191,'tve_revision_tve_has_typefocus','0'),(2956,191,'tve_revision_tve_updated_post','<div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_contentbox_shortcode thrv-content-box\">\n<div class=\"tve-content-box-background\"></div>\n<div class=\"tve-cb tve_empty_dropzone\"><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><h4 class=\"\">How Do I Apply For Social Security Disability Benefits?</h4></div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f736d232f\">You can apply for disability benefits through the Social Security Administration directly here: https://www.ssa.gov/disabilityssi/.&nbsp;</p></div></div>\n</div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_contentbox_shortcode thrv-content-box\">\n<div class=\"tve-content-box-background\"></div>\n<div class=\"tve-cb tve_empty_dropzone\"><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><h4 class=\"\">What Are The Odds To Receive Approval?</h4></div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f736d3d1a\">Data from the Social Security Administration tells us that 65% of first time applications are initially denied. At the hearing level, 54% of people are denied Nationally.&nbsp;</p></div></div>\n</div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_contentbox_shortcode thrv-content-box\">\n<div class=\"tve-content-box-background\"></div>\n<div class=\"tve-cb tve_empty_dropzone\"><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><h4 class=\"\">What Do I Need To Apply For Disability Benefits?</h4></div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f736d6c8d\">From the Social Security Administration, you need the following information: Birth and citizenship , marriage or divorce, children, U.S. Military Service, employer details, self employment details, banking information, medical condition references, medical conditions, treating doctors and specialists, medical records, job history, any education and training.&nbsp;</p></div></div>\n</div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_contentbox_shortcode thrv-content-box\">\n<div class=\"tve-content-box-background\"></div>\n<div class=\"tve-cb tve_empty_dropzone\"><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><h4 class=\"\">Why Do Initial Applications Have A High Rate of Denial?</h4></div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f736d8467\">The Social Security Administration might deny an applicant who has a valid case for several reasons:<br>• Missing or not enough medical documentation of condition in application<br>• Application was not completed correctly<br>• Applicant is working above Substantial Gainful Activity (SGA) levels earning more than $1,090 per month.<br>• Applicant is not seeking regular medical treatment with a doctor or medical expert<br>• Applicant’s disabling condition is curable in under a year</p></div></div>\n</div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_contentbox_shortcode thrv-content-box\">\n<div class=\"tve-content-box-background\"></div>\n<div class=\"tve-cb tve_empty_dropzone\"><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><h4 class=\"\">What Are The Fees If I Hire An Attorney?<em>​</em></h4></div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f736d9dfd\">Federally regulated by the Social Security Administration itself and applies to all attorneys or disability advocates, the attorney receives one-fourth of the back due benefits or $6,000 whichever is less if the claimant wins. Should the claimant lose the case, there are no fees involved and the attorney or advocate incurs all costs.</p></div></div>\n</div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_contentbox_shortcode thrv-content-box\">\n<div class=\"tve-content-box-background\"></div>\n<div class=\"tve-cb tve_empty_dropzone\"><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><h4 class=\"\">How Long To Receive An Answer From Social Security?</h4></div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f736dba98\">The initial application process takes 30 to 90 days for the initial decision. If denied, an individual has 65 days to file a request for reconsideration and will take another 30 to 90 days to receive a decision from the SSA. The application processing time varies depending on your medical condition(s), documentation provided, and whether or not you were denied and would like to file an appeal.</p></div></div>\n</div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_contentbox_shortcode thrv-content-box\">\n<div class=\"tve-content-box-background\"></div>\n<div class=\"tve-cb tve_empty_dropzone\"><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><h4 class=\"\">What Are The Work Requirements to Be Eligible For Social Security Disability Insurance Program?</h4></div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f73728336\">In order to become eligible for the Social Security Disability Insurance Program, you must have worked full time for 20 of the last 40 quarters. This translates to 5 of the last 10 years. This does not have to consecutive employment, for example: If you work full time for 3yrs, took 2 yrs off, then worked full time for one year, took 2 years off, then worked full time for another year, you would satisfy the requirements.&nbsp;</p></div></div>\n</div>'),(2957,191,'tve_revision_tve_has_wistia_popover','0'),(2958,192,'thrive_post_fonts','[]'),(2959,192,'_menu_item_type','post_type'),(2960,192,'_menu_item_menu_item_parent','0'),(2961,192,'_menu_item_object_id','186'),(2962,192,'_menu_item_object','page'),(2963,192,'_menu_item_target',''),(2964,192,'_menu_item_classes','a:1:{i:0;s:0:\"\";}'),(2965,192,'_menu_item_xfn',''),(2966,192,'_menu_item_url',''),(2968,192,'_menu_item_post_gallery',''),(2969,192,'_menu_item_subcat_gallery',''),(2970,193,'thrive_post_fonts','[]'),(2971,193,'tcb2_ready','1'),(2972,193,'_edit_last','1'),(2973,193,'_wp_page_template','default'),(2974,194,'tve_revision_tve_landing_page',''),(2975,194,'tve_revision_tve_content_before_more',''),(2976,194,'tve_revision_tve_content_more_found',''),(2977,194,'tve_revision_tve_save_post',''),(2978,194,'tve_revision_tve_custom_css',''),(2979,194,'tve_revision_tve_user_custom_css',''),(2980,194,'tve_revision_tve_page_events',''),(2981,194,'tve_revision_tve_globals',''),(2982,194,'tve_revision_tve_global_scripts',''),(2983,194,'tve_revision_thrive_icon_pack',''),(2984,194,'tve_revision_thrive_tcb_post_fonts',''),(2985,194,'tve_revision_tve_has_masonry',''),(2986,194,'tve_revision_tve_has_typefocus',''),(2987,194,'tve_revision_tve_updated_post',''),(2988,194,'tve_revision_tve_has_wistia_popover',''),(2989,193,'_thrive_meta_social_data_title',''),(2990,193,'_thrive_meta_social_data_description',''),(2991,193,'_thrive_meta_social_image',''),(2992,193,'_thrive_meta_social_twitter_username',''),(2993,193,'_thrive_meta_post_share_buttons','default'),(2994,193,'_thrive_meta_show_post_title','1'),(2995,193,'_thrive_meta_post_breadcrumbs','default'),(2996,193,'_thrive_meta_post_featured_image','default'),(2997,193,'_thrive_meta_post_header_scripts',''),(2998,193,'_thrive_meta_post_body_scripts',''),(2999,193,'_thrive_meta_post_body_scripts_top',''),(3000,193,'_thrive_meta_post_custom_css',''),(3001,193,'_thrive_meta_post_focus_area_top','default'),(3002,193,'_thrive_meta_post_focus_area_bottom','default'),(3003,193,'_thrive_ad_group_header','default'),(3004,193,'_thrive_ad_group_beginning','default'),(3005,193,'_thrive_ad_group_end_of_post','default'),(3006,193,'_edit_lock','1509470807:1'),(3007,195,'tve_revision_tve_landing_page',''),(3008,195,'tve_revision_tve_content_before_more','<div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_contentbox_shortcode thrv-content-box\">\n<div class=\"tve-content-box-background\"></div>\n<div class=\"tve-cb tve_empty_dropzone\"><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><h4 class=\"\">How Do I Apply For Social Security Disability Benefits?</h4></div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f736d232f\">You can apply for disability benefits through the Social Security Administration directly here: https://www.ssa.gov/disabilityssi/.&nbsp;</p></div></div>\n</div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_contentbox_shortcode thrv-content-box\">\n<div class=\"tve-content-box-background\"></div>\n<div class=\"tve-cb tve_empty_dropzone\"><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><h4 class=\"\">What Are The Qualifications to be Eligible For Social Security Disability Insurance?</h4></div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><p>According to the Social Security Administration (SSA)</p><ul class=\"\"><li>they have a physical or mental condition that prevents them from engaging in any \"substantial gainful activity\" (\"SGA\"), and</li><li>the condition is expected to last at least 12 months or result in death, and</li><li data-css=\"tve-u-15f737d7257\">they are under the age of 65, and</li><li>generally, they have accumulated 20 social security credits in the last 10 years prior to the onset of disability (normally four credits per full or partial year); one additional credit is required for every year by which the worker\'s age exceeds 42.</li></ul></div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_contentbox_shortcode thrv-content-box\">\n<div class=\"tve-content-box-background\"></div>\n<div class=\"tve-cb tve_empty_dropzone\"><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><h4>How Does Someone Accumulate 20 Social Security Credits?</h4></div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f73728336\">What this equates to is a person must have worked full time for 20 of the last 40 quarters. This translates to 5 of the last 10 years. This does not have to consecutive employment, for example: If you work full time for 3yrs, took 2 yrs off, then worked full time for one year, took 2 years off, then worked full time for another year, you would satisfy the requirements.&nbsp;</p></div></div>\n</div></div>\n</div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_contentbox_shortcode thrv-content-box\">\n<div class=\"tve-content-box-background\"></div>\n<div class=\"tve-cb tve_empty_dropzone\"><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><h4 class=\"\">What Are The Odds To Receive Approval?</h4></div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f736d3d1a\">Data from the Social Security Administration tells us that 65% of first time applications are initially denied. At the hearing level, 54% of people are denied Nationally.&nbsp;</p></div></div>\n</div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_contentbox_shortcode thrv-content-box\">\n<div class=\"tve-content-box-background\"></div>\n<div class=\"tve-cb tve_empty_dropzone\"><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><h4 class=\"\">What Do I Need To Apply For Disability Benefits?</h4></div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f736d6c8d\">From the Social Security Administration, you need the following information: Birth and citizenship , marriage or divorce, children, U.S. Military Service, employer details, self employment details, banking information, medical condition references, medical conditions, treating doctors and specialists, medical records, job history, any education and training.&nbsp;</p></div></div>\n</div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_contentbox_shortcode thrv-content-box\">\n<div class=\"tve-content-box-background\"></div>\n<div class=\"tve-cb tve_empty_dropzone\"><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><h4 class=\"\">Why Do Initial Applications Have A High Rate of Denial?</h4></div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f736d8467\">The Social Security Administration might deny an applicant who has a valid case for several reasons:<br>• Missing or not enough medical documentation of condition in application<br>• Application was not completed correctly<br>• Applicant is working above Substantial Gainful Activity (SGA) levels earning more than $1,090 per month.<br>• Applicant is not seeking regular medical treatment with a doctor or medical expert<br>• Applicant’s disabling condition is curable in under a year</p></div></div>\n</div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_contentbox_shortcode thrv-content-box\">\n<div class=\"tve-content-box-background\"></div>\n<div class=\"tve-cb tve_empty_dropzone\"><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><h4 class=\"\">What Are The Fees If I Hire An Attorney?<em>​</em></h4></div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f736d9dfd\">Federally regulated by the Social Security Administration itself and applies to all attorneys or disability advocates, the attorney receives one-fourth of the back due benefits or $6,000 whichever is less if the claimant wins. Should the claimant lose the case, there are no fees involved and the attorney or advocate incurs all costs.</p></div></div>\n</div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_contentbox_shortcode thrv-content-box\">\n<div class=\"tve-content-box-background\"></div>\n<div class=\"tve-cb tve_empty_dropzone\"><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><h4 class=\"\">How Long To Receive An Answer From Social Security?</h4></div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f736dba98\">The initial application process takes 30 to 90 days for the initial decision. If denied, an individual has 65 days to file a request for reconsideration and will take another 30 to 90 days to receive a decision from the SSA. The application processing time varies depending on your medical condition(s), documentation provided, and whether or not you were denied and would like to file an appeal.</p></div></div>\n</div>'),(3009,195,'tve_revision_tve_content_more_found',''),(3010,195,'tve_revision_tve_save_post',''),(3011,195,'tve_revision_tve_custom_css','@media (min-width: 300px){[data-css=\"tve-u-15f737d7257\"] { line-height: 1.75em !important; }#tve_editor [data-css=\"tve-u-15f737d7257\"] { font-size: 17px !important; }[data-css=\"tve-u-15f73728336\"] { line-height: 1.75em !important; }#tve_editor [data-css=\"tve-u-15f73728336\"] { font-size: 17px !important; }[data-css=\"tve-u-15f736dba98\"] { line-height: 1.75em !important; }#tve_editor [data-css=\"tve-u-15f736dba98\"] { font-size: 17px !important; }[data-css=\"tve-u-15f736d9dfd\"] { line-height: 1.75em !important; }#tve_editor [data-css=\"tve-u-15f736d9dfd\"] { font-size: 17px !important; }[data-css=\"tve-u-15f736d8467\"] { line-height: 1.75em !important; }#tve_editor [data-css=\"tve-u-15f736d8467\"] { font-size: 17px !important; }[data-css=\"tve-u-15f736d6c8d\"] { line-height: 1.75em !important; }#tve_editor [data-css=\"tve-u-15f736d6c8d\"] { font-size: 17px !important; }[data-css=\"tve-u-15f736d3d1a\"] { line-height: 1.75em !important; }#tve_editor [data-css=\"tve-u-15f736d3d1a\"] { font-size: 17px !important; }#tve_editor [data-css=\"tve-u-15f736d232f\"] { font-size: 17px !important; }[data-css=\"tve-u-15f736d232f\"] { line-height: 1.75em !important; }}'),(3012,195,'tve_revision_tve_user_custom_css',''),(3013,195,'tve_revision_tve_page_events','a:0:{}'),(3014,195,'tve_revision_tve_globals','a:2:{s:1:\"e\";s:1:\"1\";s:8:\"font_cls\";a:0:{}}'),(3015,195,'tve_revision_tve_global_scripts',''),(3016,195,'tve_revision_thrive_icon_pack','0'),(3017,195,'tve_revision_thrive_tcb_post_fonts','a:0:{}'),(3018,195,'tve_revision_tve_has_masonry','0'),(3019,195,'tve_rev