r thrv-columns\"><div class=\"tcb-flex-row tcb--cols--1\"><div class=\"tcb-flex-col\"><div class=\"tcb-col tve_empty_dropzone\"><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\" data-css=\"tve-u-15f73c6a5d7\"><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f7817ad79\">Current data from the SSA estimates wait times for appeal hearings to take over 600 days, or nearly 20 months.&nbsp;</p><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f7817b851\">Every month of waiting was another month that Sterling was pulling from his life’s reserves to cover daily expenses, slowly draining his savings account. “I wasn’t sleeping, I was constantly worrying,” Sterling said.&nbsp;</p><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f7817c24f\">“I was the breadwinner, and I needed to be able to provide for my family. It killed me that I wasn’t able to do that.”In need of another option, Sterling turned online for legal advice. “A friend recommended I look for an advocacy group, but that sounded expensive. I already couldn’t afford my bills,” he said. “I certainly didn’t think I could afford help.”<br><br></p></div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\" data-css=\"tve-u-15f73c6a5d7\"><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f7817f4d6\">But online, he learned that disability attorneys and advocate groups such as the <strong><em>Social Security Claim Advocates</em></strong> are paid only a small percentage of back disability payments, and only after a client’s application is approved.</p><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f7818014b\">These payments are capped at 25 percent and limited to $6,000 by law. For this reason, many advocacy groups are extremely selective about their clients, and they take cases that they expect to win. If their client is never approved for disability benefits, the client doesn’t pay a dime.</p><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f781810cb\">And though disability advocacy does not guarantee a faster approval process, professional groups like these can vastly reduce the time lost due to technical errors and refiling—one of the top reasons for first-time denials—and greatly improve the chances of a favorable outcome.</p></div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\" data-css=\"tve-u-15f7dfffb99\"><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f78182061\">Sterling said he didn’t mind paying after the approval for the immense peace of mind he gained. “Knowing that I had a group of experts fighting for my case meant that I could finally sleep at night.</p><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f78182b2e\">I gave myself the best chance of a good outcome.” The best outcome was what Sterling, and the many other disability applicants every year who seek out help, received. Advocacy groups and disability attorneys build sophisticated cases for their clients to ensure that applications make it through all the hoops, and in today’s complex system, it truly takes an expert.</p><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f78183804\">“You can’t do it on your own these days,” Sterling said. “My advocacy group gave me so much help and reassurance. I could have saved myself months of unnecessary anxiety if I had just known that sooner.”<br><br></p></div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_heading\"><h1 data-css=\"tve-u-15f7e1d9409\">If You Need Help and Want To Learn More About Advocacy Groups like, <em>Social Security Claim Advocates&nbsp;</em>to See If They Will Take Your Case, Click Below:</h1></div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv-button\" data-css=\"tve-u-15f7e19144e\">\n<a href=\"http://ssclaimadvocates.com\" class=\"tcb-button-link\" onclick=\"ga(\'send\',\'event\',\'clicks\',\'SSClaim_Advocates_Click\',\'SSDI_Leads\');return\" true;\"\"=\"\" <span=\"\"><span class=\"tcb-button-text thrv-inline-text\">Click Here To Qualify</span>\n</a>\n</div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv-page-section\">\n<div class=\"tve-page-section-out\" data-css=\"tve-u-15f73c2f915\"></div>\n<div class=\"tve-page-section-in tve_empty_dropzone\" data-css=\"tve-u-15f73c2a4e4\"><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\" data-css=\"tve-u-15f73c67d17\"><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f73c64b30\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><u>Advertiser Disclosure:&nbsp;&nbsp;</u>SSDInsider is a consumer information site that offers free articles and information relating to Social Security Disability. Many of the companies whose services we mention provide us compensation when someone who clicks from our site becomes their customer. This is how we make money to support our site. Compensation may impact which companies we write about and which articles those companies appear. We do not mention all companies that provide a given service All opinions expressed on this site are our own.</p></div></div>\n</div>'),(4078,262,'tve_revision_tve_content_more_found',''),(4079,262,'tve_revision_tve_save_post',''),(4080,262,'tve_revision_tve_custom_css','@media (min-width: 300px){[data-css=\"tve-u-15f7e19144e\"] { display: block; max-width: 275.333px; }[data-css=\"tve-u-15f7e1d9409\"] { line-height: 1.5em !important; }#tve_editor [data-css=\"tve-u-15f7e1d9409\"] { font-size: 26px !important; }[data-css=\"tve-u-15f7e19144e\"] .tcb-button-link { background-image: none !important; background-color: rgb(31, 84, 145) !important; min-height: 54.7619px; font-size: 1.33333em; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; }[data-css=\"tve-u-15f7cc96c32\"] + div { clear: none; }[data-css=\"tve-u-15f7cc96c32\"] { float: none; width: 768px; }[data-css=\"tve-u-15f781280f9\"] { line-height: 1.25em !important; }#tve_editor [data-css=\"tve-u-15f781280f9\"] { font-size: 2.25em !important; }[data-css=\"tve-u-15f780ffc14\"] { border: none; border-radius: 0px; overflow: hidden; margin-bottom: -37px !important; margin-right: 0px !important; padding-right: 1px !important; margin-left: 0px !important; padding-left: 1px !important; }[data-css=\"tve-u-15f73d7c1d0\"] { line-height: 35px !important; }#tve_editor [data-css=\"tve-u-15f73d7c1d0\"] { font-size: 1.75em !important; color: rgb(254, 250, 250) !important; }[data-css=\"tve-u-15f73d77486\"] { background-color: rgb(31, 84, 145)