al in the mail citing a lack of hard medical evidence in his case.</p><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f78175e97\">“My doctor told me I was unable to go back to my job,” Sterling said. “He’s my doctor. What more medical evidence do they need?”</p><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f7817680a\">Unfortunately, John Sterling’s situation is far from uncommon. Data collected from the Social Security Administration (SSA) shows that roughly 68 percent of first-time disability applicants are initially denied.</p><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f78177579\">While differing from case to case, the reasons for these denials commonly involve incorrect or incomplete applications with a lack of information. Given just 60 days to apply for an appeal, Sterling said he felt crushed and overwhelmed.</p></div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\"><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f78178728\">&nbsp;“I’m a responsible citizen. I couldn’t understand why the government wasn’t willing to help me.”</p></div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv-page-section\">\n<div class=\"tve-page-section-out\" data-css=\"tve-u-15f73d77486\"></div>\n<div class=\"tve-page-section-in tve_empty_dropzone\"><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\" data-css=\"tve-u-15f6e6b1606\"><h4 data-css=\"tve-u-15f73d7c1d0\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><strong>“I’m a responsible citizen. I couldn’t understand why the government wasn’t willing to help me.”</strong></em></h4></div></div>\n</div><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv-columns\"><div class=\"tcb-flex-row tcb--cols--1\"><div class=\"tcb-flex-col\"><div class=\"tcb-col tve_empty_dropzone\"><div class=\"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element tve_empty_dropzone\" data-css=\"tve-u-15f73c6a5d7\"><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f7817ad79\">Current data from the SSA estimates wait times for appeal hearings to take over 600 days, or nearly 20 months.&nbsp;</p><p data-css=\"tve-u-15f7817b851\">Every month of waiting was another month that Sterling was pulling from his life’s reserves to cover da