e major reasons why advocacy groups are <em>extremely selective</em> in the cases they take on.</p><p>If a person never receives approval for disability benefits, they don’t have to pay a dime. “For me I didn’t mind paying someone after I won approval if it meant peace of mind.”, John said. “It was like I could finally sleep at night knowing that there was a group fighting for me, making sure everything was done correctly”.</p><p>Although disability advocacy groups cannot guarantee a quicker approval, they can reduce the time lost having to refile due to technical errors, which as mentioned above, is one of the major reasons for first time denials. “I’m happy with how everything turned out” said John. “If I was going through this process again, I would get on the phone with an advocacy group right away to see if they could help, it would have saved me months of unnecessary anxiety”.</p><p>To learn more about advocacy groups like the one mentioned in this article, <a href=\"https://www.disability-benefits-help.org/cpc/about-ssdi?utm_source=google&amp;utm_medium=cpc&amp;utm_term=disability%20benefits&amp;utm_content=225101598144&amp;utm_campaign=SSD+-+Phrase+Always&amp;__egma[MatchType]=p&amp;__egma[Network]=g&amp;__egma[Device]=c&amp;__egma[Creative]=225101598144&amp;__egma[Placement]=&amp;__egma[AdPosition]=1t1&amp;gclid=EAIaIQobChMI-_2d2KaM1wIVF7jACh0fsQS1EAAYASAAEgId3_D_BwE\"><u>click here</u></a></p>','DENIED! How 428,654 Disabled Americans Are Using A Little Understood Resource To Finally Get Their Disability Benefits Approved','','inherit','closed','closed','','63-revision-v1','','','2017-10-25 17:39:19','2017-10-25 17:39:19','',63,'https://ssdinsider.com/2017/10/25/63-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(73,1,'2017-10-25 17:39:41','2017-10-25 17:39:41','<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\">DENIED! How 428,654 Disabled Americans Are Using A <em>Little Understood</em> Resource To Finally Get Their Disability Benefits Approved.</h1>\r\nOctober 27, 2017 Boston, MA:America