cessary anxiety if I had just known that sooner.”</p><p>If you want to learn more about advocacy groups like Disability United to see if they can help you or a loved one, click here.</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><u>Advertiser Disclosure:&nbsp;&nbsp;</u>SSDInsider is a consumer information site that offers free articles and information relating to Social Security Disability. Many of the companies whose services we mention provide us compensation when someone who clicks from our site becomes their customer. This is how we make money to support our site. Compensation may impact which companies we write about and which articles those companies appear. We do not mention all companies that provide a given service All opinions expressed on this site are our own.</p>','Has This 52 Year Old Disabled American Found The Secret To Disability Benefits Approval?','','inherit','closed','closed','','77-revision-v1','','','2017-11-01 15:33:50','2017-11-01 15:33:50','',77,'https://ssdinsider.com/2017/11/01/77-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(250,1,'2017-11-02 02:16:32','2017-11-02 02:16:32','[tcb-script]fbq(\'track\', \'ViewContent\', {value: 2,currency: \'USD\',});[/tcb-script]<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">Has This 52 Year Old Disabled American Found The Secret To Disability Benefits Approval?</h1><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>By Disability Insider</strong>November 1, 2017<strong>Time Required:</strong> 2 Minutes</p><p>“You never think it will happen to you – and then it does.”John Sterling is recalling his reaction when he received the news that he would never return to work.</p><p>&nbsp;But Sterling wasn’t laid off – he was one of 375,000 Americans every year who are retired by their doctors for disabilities. He, like many Americans, never planned for the abrupt brain aneurysm that would change his life.</p><p>The government, however, does plan, and a tiny percentage of Sterling’s wages have been paid into the Disability Insurance Trust Fund since the program 